# UI Building Rules

ALWAYS use shadcn/ui components for ANY UI work. Never write custom buttons, inputs, cards, dialogs, dropdowns, tabs, or any other primitive from scratch.

# Workflow

1. Before building any UI, call the shadcn MCP to see what components are available
2. If a needed component isn't installed in `components/ui/`, install it via the MCP
3. Compose pages and features from shadcn components — do not reinvent primitives
4. For pre-built sections (auth pages, dashboards, settings), check shadcn blocks first via the MCP

# Styling

- Tailwind utility classes only
- Use shadcn's CSS variables for colors (e.g., `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`) — never hardcode colors
- Use `lucide-react` for all icons
- Follow shadcn composition patterns (Card → CardHeader/CardContent/CardFooter, Form → FormField/FormItem/FormLabel/FormControl)

# Forms

- Always use `react-hook-form` with `zod` for validation
- Use shadcn's Form components, not raw inputs